song_name: Your Only Friends Are Make Believe

version_description: Pretty basic song to play. A good one for beginners who also happen to be Gin Blossom fans.
Includes measure markers, intro chords, break chords, correct lyrics and chords.
Added riffs and corrected the chorus so the riffs make sense.
This song is in the key of G.

This gives the feel of the multiple guitar parts played as chords so should work for playing solo acoustic or in a band. You can also play the 2nd guitar riff throughout the verses adding a high G for the 2nd part of each verse. If you do this use index finger for the alternating bass line, middle finger for the D (B string), small finger for the B (G string) so you can then add the ring finger for the high G (e string) for the 2nd part of each verse. Can also finger pick the chords playing the bass note first and then descending arpeggios for the top strings and again add a high G for the 2nd part of each verse.
This version is for acoustic playing.
